  "subject": "docs: runbooks (wraparound, cyfronet bootstrap, component recipe) + cyfronet hydrator app",
  "body": "- docs/runbooks/xid-wraparound.md: diagnosis/recovery/prevention for the E4\n  transaction-ID wraparound incident class the LandingDBXidAgeHigh alert\n  guards against.\n- docs/runbooks/bootstrap-cyfronet.md: mirrors hack/kind-up.sh for the real\n  cluster -- write-capable SSH deploy key (SOPS-encrypted), ESO\n  ClusterSecretStore against GCP Secret Manager, Lakekeeper encryption key\n  via ExternalSecret, and the environments/cyfronet-next -> cyfronet PR gate.\n- docs/runbooks/adding-a-component.md: the two extension recipes (authored\n  chart resource vs. upstream operator Application) and the common\n  EXPECTED_APPS/lint/kind-verify tail both end with.\n- environments/cyfronet/apps/datalake.yaml: the datalake-cyfronet Source\n  Hydrator Application (values.yaml + values-cyfronet.yaml, syncSource\n  environments/cyfronet, hydrateTo environments/cyfronet-next).\n- environments/cyfronet/argocd-values.yaml: cyfronet ArgoCD bootstrap values\n  (kind's minus server.insecure, plus resource requests).\n- Makefile: sops-setup target (age keypair -> .sops.yaml recipient), needed\n  for the bootstrap-cyfronet runbook's SOPS flow to actually be runnable.\n"
}
